'''Serdar Roşan''' (born 1958), is a contemporary [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] writer, poet and translator. He was born in [[Diyarbakir]] and after the 1980 [[coup]] emigrated to [[Sweden]]. He has published two books of poetry and three collections of short stories and Kurdish legends. He has also translated nine books from foreign languages into Kurdish including classic works by [[Cervantes]], [[Guy de Maupassant]], [[Ernest Hemingway]] and [[Jack London]].<ref>[http://www.nefel.nu/articles/article_detail.asp?RubricNr=7&ArticleNr=2606 An Interview with Serdar Roşan], By [[Enwer Karahan]], Nefel.com, 2007. (in Kurdish)</ref> He is a member of the Association of Kurdish Writers in Sweden.<ref>[http://www.niviskar.se/kurdi/Endam/serdar_rosan/48.html Serdar Roşan] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101215004306/http://www.niviskar.se/kurdi/Endam/serdar_rosan/48.html |date=2010-12-15 }}, ''Komeleya Nivîskarên Kurd li Swêdê'' (in Kurdish).</ref>
==Books== #''Çîrokên hezar û şevekê'', 143 pp., Nûdem Publishers, Sweden, 1998.<ref>[http://www.institutkurde.org/products/details/229/]</ref> #''Bi xatirê silehan'', translation of [[A Farewell to Arms]], 345 pp., Nûdem Publishers, Sweden, 2000, {{ISBN|978-91-88592-50-7}}. #''Mircana qelew'', translation of [[Boule de suif]], 127 pp., Nûdem Publishers, Sweden, 2000, {{ISBN|978-91-88592-49-1}}.<ref>[http://public.pulsen.se/boras/post.asp?FILIAL=FHH&PID=388163 Mircana qelew]{{dead link|date=May 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, Borås Stadsbiblioteket.</ref> #''Destanên Kurdî: ji zargotina kurdî'', A Collection of Kurdish legends, with [[Reşo Zîlan]], Kurdish Cultural Foundation in Stockholm, 2004, {{ISBN|978-975-6282-30-4}}. #''Dara gozê'', Collection of short stories, 133 pp., Doz Publishers, Istanbul, 2005, {{ISBN|978-975-6876-58-9}}. #''Bazên welat'', Poems, 64 pp., Doz Publishers, Istanbul, 2005, {{ISBN|978-975-6876-57-2}}. #''Xencer'', Poems, 64 pp., Doz Publishers, Istanbul, 2007, {{ISBN|978-9944-2-2721-6}}.<ref>[http://www.kibo.com.tr/kibokatalog/kibodetay.php?pid=653340]</ref> #''Don Kîşot'', translation of [[Don Quijote]], 519 pp., Doz Publishers, Istanbul, 2007, {{ISBN|978-9944-2-2726-1}}.<ref>[http://www.kibo.com.tr/kibokatalog/kibodetay.php?pid=653318 DON KİŞOT]</ref>
