{{Infobox language |name = Western Persian |altname = Farsi |nativename = {{lang|fa|فارسی}} |pronunciation = {{IPA-fa|fɒːɾˈsiː|}} |states = [[Iran]], [[Iraq]] |region = [[Western Asia]] |speakers = 55.6 million |date=2015 |ref=e18 |familycolor = Indo-European |fam2 = [[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3 = [[Iranian languages|Iranian]] |fam4 = [[Western Iranian languages|Western Iranian]] |fam5 = [[Southwestern Iranian languages|Southwestern Iranian]] |fam6 = [[Persian language|Persian]] |dialects =[[Abadani Persian|Abadani]], [[Arak, Iran|Araki]], [[Bandar-Abbas|Bandari]], [[Isfahan|Esfahani]], [[Karbala]]i, [[Kashan]]i, [[Kerman]]i, [[Mashhad]]i, [[Qazvin]]i, [[Shiraz]]i, [[Tehrani accent|Tehrani]], [[Yazd]]i |script = [[Persian alphabet|Perso-Arabic script]] |nation = Iran |agency = [[Academy of Persian Language and Literature]] |iso3 = pes |glotto=west2369 |glottorefname=Western Farsi |notice = IPA }}
{{Contains Perso-Arabic text}}
'''Western Persian''' or '''Iranian Persian''' is the most widely spoken dialect of [[Persian language|Persian]].<ref name=UC>{{cite web|title=Persian|url=http://www.langcen.cam.ac.uk/resources/persian/persian.php|publisher=[[University of Cambridge]]|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref> It is spoken in [[Iran]] and by minorities in [[Iraq]] and the [[Arab states of the Persian Gulf|Persian Gulf]] states.<ref name=UC/> It is one of three major dialects of Persian.
Western Persian is also known as ''Iranian Persian'', ''Farsi'',<ref name=UC/> ''Western Farsi'', or simply ''Persian''.
