{{Esperanto sidebar |expanded=Language}}
[[File:Jcircumflex.png|thumb|J with circumflex in [[Doulos SIL]]]]
'''Ĵ''' or '''ĵ''' (J [[circumflex]]) is a letter in [[Esperanto orthography]] representing the sound {{IPAblink|ʒ}}.

While Esperanto orthography uses a [[diacritic]] for its four postalveolar consonants, as do the Latin-based [[Slavic languages|Slavic]] alphabets, the base letters are Romano-Germanic. ''Ĵ'' is based on the [[French language|French]] pronunciation of the letter ''[[j]]'' to better preserve the shape of borrowings from that language (such as ''ĵurnalo'' from ''journal'') than Slavic ''[[ž]]'' would.

{{H-system|Ĵ|ĵ|J|j|fourteenth}}

==Usage==

===In mathematics===
* The letter <math>\boldsymbol{\hat{\jmath}}</math> is sometimes used to denote a [[unit vector]] in mathematics.

